@startuml 05-sequence-listen-server

title NetMode ListenServer (client host spawns Rex.Server child)

skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.2
skinparam maxMessageSize 220

actor User

box "Rex.Client process" #E8F4FC
  participant Program <<control>> as Prog
  participant ClientApp <<control>> as App
end box

participant "Rex.Server child process" <<boundary>> as Child

note over User, Child
  ListenServer is not a NetMode value passed into ClientApp.
  Rex.Client starts Rex.Server as a separate OS process then runs ClientApp as NetMode Client to localhost.
  In-game packets match 05-sequence-client-remote.puml after the child prints the ready line.
end note

== Start child server ==

User -> Prog : Main(args with ListenServer)
activate Prog
Prog -> Child : Process.Start(Rex.Server)
activate Child
note right of Child
  Child runs ServerApp.Run.
  That constructs GameServer and calls Start.
end note
Child -> Child : ServerApp.Run
Child -> Child : GameServer.Start
Child ->> Prog : stdout ProtocolConstants.ListenProcessReadyLine
deactivate Child

== Run local client ==

Prog -> App : new ClientApp(NetMode.Client)
activate App
Prog -> App : Run(127.0.0.1, port)
note right of App
  Run blocks until the client stops.
  Connect and steady state follow the Client remote diagram.
end note

== Teardown ==

App --> Prog
deactivate App
Prog -> Child : stop child Process
activate Child
Child -> Child : process exit
deactivate Child
deactivate Prog

@enduml
